# Frontend Host Configuration

# No environment variables are required for the frontend build or runtime.
#
# The application communicates with backend microservices using relative endpoints:
#   - Auth Service:       /api/auth
#   - Employee Service:   /api/employee
#   - Purchasing Service: /api/purchasing
#
# In DEVELOPMENT:
#   Vite's configuration (vite.config.js) automatically proxies these calls to local host ports (8001, 8002, 8003).
#
# In PRODUCTION:
#   The Docker container serves static files via Nginx, which proxies these endpoints to backend Docker containers.
#
# If you ever need to introduce build-time configurations, specify them using the VITE_ prefix:
# VITE_EXAMPLE_VARIABLE=value
